{{refimprove|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox football league season | image = LFFPirmaLyga.jpg | competition = [[I Lyga]] | season = 2015 | winners = [[FK Jonava|Lietava]] | relegated = | matches = | total goals = | league topscorer = Laurynas Stonkus | biggest home win = [[FC Žalgiris|Žalgiris B]] 12–0 [[FK Tauras Tauragė|Tauras]] | biggest away win = [[FK Tauras Tauragė|Tauras]] 2–8 [[FK Šilutė|Šilutė]] | highest scoring = [[FC Žalgiris|Žalgiris B]] 12–0 [[FK Tauras Tauragė|Tauras]] | longest wins = | longest unbeaten = | longest winless = | longest losses = | highest attendance = | lowest attendance = | attendance = | average attendance = | prevseason = [[2014 LFF I Lyga|2014]] | nextseason = [[2016 LFF I Lyga|2016]] | extra information = }}
'''2015 LFF I Lyga''' was a Lithuanian second-tier football league season which started on March 28, 2015 and finished on October 31. It consisted of 18 teams.
