{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Fylkisvöllur''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Reykjavík]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/iceland.shtml|title=World Stadiums - Stadiums in Iceland|website=www.worldstadiums.com|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref> [[Iceland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://soccer365.me/stadiums/1085/|title=Stadium "Fylkisvöllur" (Iceland) - information, videos, news, map, weather - Soccer365.me|website=soccer365.me|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref>  It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://citymaps.com/v/is/is/reykjavik/fylkisvollur/a6cf2bca-0614-4983-89c8-b8044ef190b7|title=Fylkisvöllur|website=citymaps.com|access-date=2016-07-08|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160808054121/https://citymaps.com/v/is/is/reykjavik/fylkisvollur/a6cf2bca-0614-4983-89c8-b8044ef190b7|archivedate=2016-08-08|df=}}</ref>  The stadium holds roughly 1800 spectators seated. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.football-lineups.com/stadium/2266/|title=Fylkisvöllur - Football Stadium|website=Football-Lineups|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref>
The name for the stadium was changed to Flórídanavöllurinn in 2015 due to sponsorship reasons

