{{Use Pakistani English|date=April 2018}} {{refimprove|date=August 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox cricket team | name = Lahore Thunder | alt_name = LT | image = Lahore_Thunder.jpg | alt = 200px | captain = Mudassar Shah | coach = | city = [[Lahore]], [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]] | colors = [[Orange (color)|Orange]] and [[Blue]] | owner = Ali Akbar Group, Sayban Group, Tara Group | founded = 2018 }}
'''Lahore Thunder (LT)''' is a [[Kabaddi]] club based in [[Lahore]], [[Pakistan]] that plays in the [[Super Kabaddi League]]. The team is currently led by Mudassar Shah.<ref>{{cite web|last=Rehman |first=Dawood |url=https://en.dailypakistan.com.pk/sports/pakistan-all-set-for-first-ever-super-kabaddi-league-also-featuring-women-teams/ |title=Pakistan’s first ever Super Kabaddi League features two women teams – Daily Pakistan |publisher=En.dailypakistan.com.pk |date=2018-04-30 |accessdate=2018-05-23}}</ref>
==Franchise history== Super Kabaddi League (SKL) is a professional [[Kabaddi]] league in Pakistan, based on the format of the group games and eliminator. The first edition of the tournament was played in 2018 with ten franchises representing various cities in Pakistan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/309278-10-foreign-players-to-feature-in-pak-super-kabaddi-league |title=10 foreign players to feature in Pak Super Kabaddi League &#124; Sports &#124; thenews.com.pk &#124; Lahore |publisher=thenews.com.pk |date=2018-04-26 |accessdate=2018-05-23}}</ref>
It has a dedicated following in [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|NY]] and [[Tampa, Florida|Tampa Bay]], [[Florida|FL]].
