{{update|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox country at games | IAAF = LTU | fedname = [[Lietuvos lengvosios atletikos federacija]] | year = 2013 | games = World Championships in Athletics | location = [[Moscow]] | competitors = 14 | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | rank = | previous = [[Lithuania at the 2011 World Championships in Athletics|2011]] | next = [[Lithuania at the 2015 World Championships in Athletics|2015]] | website = {{URL|http://www.lengvoji.lt/}} }}
'''[[Lithuania]]''' competed at the '''[[2013 World Championships in Athletics]]''' in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]], from 10–18 August 2013.
== Qualification standards == 18 athletes from Lithuania in total achieved qualification standards: [[Marius Žiūkas]] (A, 20&nbsp;km walk), [[Tadas Šuškevičius]] (A, 50&nbsp;km walk; B, 20&nbsp;km walk), [[Tomas Gaidamavičius]] (B, 50&nbsp;km walk), [[Ričardas Rekst]] (B, 50&nbsp;km walk), [[Rasa Drazdauskaitė]] (Marathon), [[Diana Lobačevskė]] (Marathon), [[Remalda Kergytė]] (Marathon), [[Živilė Balčiūnaitė]] (Marathon), [[Austra Skujytė]] (A, Heptathlon), [[Kristina Saltanovič]] (A, 20&nbsp;km walk), [[Brigita Virbalytė]] (A, 20&nbsp;km walk), [[Neringa Aidietytė]] (A, 20&nbsp;km walk), [[Virgilijus Alekna]] (B, discus throw), [[Zinaida Sendriūtė]] (A, discus throw), [[Agnė Šerkšnienė]] (B, 400 m; B, 200 m), [[Lina Grinčikaitė]] (B, 100 m), [[Airinė Palšytė]] (B, high jump), [[Eglė Balčiūnaitė]] (A, 800 m).
''<small>notes: Austra Skujytė and Rasa Drazauskaitė won't participate, Tomas Gaidamavičius and Ričardas Rekst can't enter because of B standards.</small>''
