'''Tacuarembó Fútbol Club''', usually known simply as '''Tacuarembó''', are a [[Uruguay]]an [[football (soccer)|football]] club based in [[Tacuarembó]].

==History==
Like the inner-country team Rocha, Tacuarembó is a super merge of 21 different clubs, and represents all of the department it is located in, except for the city of [[Paso de los Toros]]. The team was relegated to the [[Uruguayan Segunda División|Second Division]] after finishing 15th in the [[2010–11 Uruguayan Primera División season|2010–11 season]].

